    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get that it can be both, but it feels like people usually only talk about the bad side of it in academic circles. like, if we don't have some kind of national identity, doesn't that just lead to society falling apart into smaller, more bitter factions? isn't a certain amount of nationalism basically required for a country to function?",
