      "content": "A strong sense of national identity, rooted in shared values and a common destiny, is undeniably crucial for a large, complex society to function effectively. Without a unifying narrative, societies risk fracturing into competing tribalisms where cooperation becomes impossible. The necessary element is a civic nationalism—one based on shared laws and democratic principles—rather than an ethnic nationalism based on exclusion.",
